===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Ancient simplification of {{och-l|靁}}, which was a {{Han compound|雨|畾|ls=psc|c1=s|t1=rain|c2=p|nocap=1}}.

===Etymology===
The Northern Min initial ''s-'' may be due to the loss of a pre-initial which might have been a velar considering dialect forms in Henan, Hebei and Shanxi, e.g. Taiyuan Jin {{zh-l|忽雷|tr=hueh4 lui1}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Perhaps from {{cog|sit}}. Compare {{cog|lus|râwl||voice; cry (of an animal); sound}}, {{cog|bo|ཁྲོལ||}}.
* {{sense|spoiler}} {{clipping|zh|捏他八雷|tr=niētābāléi}}, from {{bor|zh|ja|ネタバレ|tr=netabare}}.
* {{sense|loyalty}} by homophony of {{m|yue|二||two}} and {{m|yue|義||spirit of loyalty}}.
* {{sense|to lay off}} from {{psm|zh|en|lay off}}.

